half_marathons.name: SF Half!
half_marathons.description:
Last four miles were so hard haha but I did it!
1:58:05 unofficial

half_marathons.name: Philadelphia Half Marathon
half_marathons.description: Some really bad wind from mile 7 to mile 10. Goal was sub 68 but it was just a tough day. It was hot to start then super windy. GPS was wack. Hit 10k behind my goal and just raced then. Josh Christianson and I hit 20k together and absolutely dueled it out to the finish. He got me but he had to work for it 😂. Zachary  Marmol  ran great and finished 2 spots behind Olympian Jared Ward

full_marathons.name: Boston Marathon — 2:31:45
full_marathons.description:
Minute PR!! 200th OA

Thought I went out too fast, surprised myself by holding steady through Newton hills, didn’t think I had a PR in me until 21, took a shot downhill 21-23, paid for that decision the rest of the way to the end. 

Turned onto Boylston and the watch read 2:30:00 and I thought I could become a 2:30 marathoner but damn the Boylston finish stretch is looong 😂

full_marathons.name: 2:58:xx — The David’s Greatest Philadelphia Hits Philadelphia Marathon — 1st place
full_marathons.description:
Somehow maintained sub 7’s through city streets (not a real race fyi)

Feat a negative split for once

full_marathons.name: Long Island Marathon — 2:49:07, 5th OA
full_marathons.description:
Amy Liu RAN A HUGE PR!!! BQ HERE WE COME

Ouch. Don’t try the three week turnaround, bad idea. Tough conditions

full_marathons.name: Long Island Marathon
full_marathons.description:
Confirmed: Sun/heat is the worst race condition 
Really was in despair starting at mile 18(?) and didn’t think I was going to finish. Walked a good amount on the verge of seizing with the super shoes. 
Mainly proud of just finishing but also 14 min PR!

full_marathons.name: Marine Corps Marathon
full_marathons.description: Went out WAYYY to fast and paid for it in the last 6-8 miles but hyped for this huge PR!! I set out this training block wanting a sub 4 marathon and SO glad I was able to get it done!!

broad_street_run.name: Broad Street Run
broad_street_run.description: Tough run from pretty early on. Still pretty happy. Thank you to everyone who came to cheer and volunteer! You guys are amazing

broad_street_run.name: Broad Street 2023🏙
broad_street_run.description:
Official time: 56:32

Wow such a great race! Felt so much better than I had thought and didn't rain till the last mile. Also had a massive group for the first 5 miles working together and just clicking off 5:40s. Had a great final kick off with another runner too. Absolutely love this race, now for a bit of time off before getting back at it

Also I was too harsh on the Vaporfly 3s, they felt amazing today

Boston rain 🤝 Broad Street rain

broad_street_run.name: Broad Street Run 2023
broad_street_run.description: Official results: 59.08 and 241 overall :). Arrived late and could not start at the front. Ended up going around people and twisted my ankle a bit. Hopefully is nothing. Still, good run... And the rain 🌧️🌧️🌧️. Next race: Santiago Marathon with Sol Salgado and Alonso Astroza :)
